Vegetable Bolognese  - gf, vegan

6 tbsp olive oil, divided
10 oz cremini mushrooms
1 tsp salt
1 onion, chopped
1/4 c toamto paste
5 garlic cloves, minced
1 1/4 tsp oregano
1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes
28 oz crushed tomatoes
2 c vegetable broth
1 can chickpeas, drained
2 tbsp fresh basil, chopped

Pulse mushrooms in food processor until pieces resemble pebbles (2 batches). Heat 5 tbsp olive oil in dutch oven & add mushrooms and salt; cook for 8 min. Pulse onion in food processor until minced; add to mushrooms and cook for 5 min. Add tomato paste and cook until brown in color. Mix 1 tbsp olive oil, garlic, oregano, and crushed red pepper flakes in a small bowl until everything is evenly coated; add to pot and cook until fragrant, ~30 s. Add tomatoes and broth, simmer for 5 min. Pulse chickpeas in food processor 7-9 times. Remove from processor bowl and rinse off starch. Add to the sauce and cook for 15 min covered. Remove from heat and stir in basil. Add to al dente pasta & toss to coat; serve.
